01:07.667 --> 01:09.768
   Well, at least you don't
   have to worry about them

01:09.770 --> 01:11.203
      talking over each other.

01:14.841 --> 01:18.377
        <i>♪ My little pony,</i>
         <i>my little pony ♪</i>

01:18.379 --> 01:20.312
           <i>♪ Aaaahhh </i>

01:20.314 --> 01:24.783
     <i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
      <i>friendship could be. ♪</i>

01:24.785 --> 01:29.254
      <i>♪ Until you all shared</i>
       <i>its magic with me. ♪</i>

01:29.256 --> 01:35.627
       <i>♪ Sharing kindness </i>
      <i>♪ it's an easy feat </i>

01:35.629 --> 01:37.629
       <i>♪ And magic makes it</i>
         <i>all complete! ♪</i>

01:37.631 --> 01:39.765
    <i>♪ To have my little pony </i>

01:39.767 --> 01:43.268
     <i>♪ Do you know you're all</i>
     <i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

01:43.270 --> 01:45.604
               ♪

01:50.143 --> 01:53.278
               ♪

01:57.617 --> 01:59.785
   I don't know what happened
       on that boat trip,

01:59.787 --> 02:02.454
   but once Rarity, Applejack,
  and Pinkie Pie have some tea

02:02.456 --> 02:05.491
    and talk it out, I'm sure
   everypony will feel better.

02:10.330 --> 02:11.530
                 [knock at door]

02:15.535 --> 02:18.570
Gummy, Opalescence, and
Winona? This is a surprise.

02:21.207 --> 02:23.408
     Are Pinkie Pie, Rarity
     and Applejack with you?

02:27.747 --> 02:30.382
   "Sorry darling, but I must
     decline the invitation

02:30.384 --> 02:32.151
         to your soiree.

02:32.153 --> 02:34.720
    While I'm sure it will be
     positively resplendent,

02:34.722 --> 02:37.556
  there are certain ponies I'd
    rather not associate with

02:37.558 --> 02:41.727
     at the moment. Rarity."

02:41.729 --> 02:45.197
    Rarity's not coming? Aww.

02:45.199 --> 02:47.399
 So I polished my
scales for nothing.

02:52.772 --> 02:55.407
     "Sorry I can't make it,
   but I'm still a mite upset

02:55.409 --> 02:58.544
 about everything that happened
    on the boat. Applejack."

03:00.513 --> 03:02.814
       "Sorry I can't make
      the tea party today,

03:02.816 --> 03:05.284
   but there's a small problem
      with the guest list.

03:05.286 --> 03:07.586
  Plus, I'm right in the middle
  of a very important cupcake.

03:07.588 --> 03:09.254
            Pinkie."

03:10.823 --> 03:13.325
    Come on, Spike. Since our
     friends won't come here

03:13.327 --> 03:16.295
   and tell us what happened,
 we'll just have to go to them.

03:16.297 --> 03:17.863
        Right behind you.

03:25.972 --> 03:30.776
      [gasp]I am sorry, but
       my mane wasn't made

03:30.778 --> 03:32.611
     to support marine life.

03:36.516 --> 03:39.418
   Ruined. Completely ruined.

03:39.420 --> 03:41.253
      I don't know, Rarity.
        Maybe you could--

03:41.255 --> 03:43.789
  Throw it away? Yes, I agree.

03:43.791 --> 03:47.726
 Just another innocent casualty
  of that disastrous boat trip.

03:47.728 --> 03:51.563
   Spike and I were wondering
    what happened out there.

03:53.633 --> 03:56.335
    Please, darling, I don't
    know if I'll ever be able

03:56.337 --> 03:59.938
       to discuss it. It's
        far too painful.

03:59.940 --> 04:01.673
      If it's too difficult
         to talk about,

04:01.675 --> 04:03.875
    we completely understand.

04:03.877 --> 04:05.677
         Well, since you
      dragged it out of me:

04:05.679 --> 04:08.614
         It all started
          at the docks.

04:08.616 --> 04:11.316
   I knew Applejack and Pinkie
      Pie wanted to get out

04:11.318 --> 04:14.753
     of their element, so I
  thought I would surprise them

04:14.755 --> 04:16.421
     with an elegant cruise.

04:16.423 --> 04:21.927
 I had brought a small bag with
   just a few key essentials.

04:21.928 --> 04:23.662
       All right, ponies.

04:23.664 --> 04:26.732
     Prepare yourselves for
    luxury on the high seas!

04:26.734 --> 04:29.301
That sounds... fun.

04:33.573 --> 04:36.975
  The sea air carries a portent
      for trouble this day.

04:36.977 --> 04:39.278
       T'is a treacherous
      and perilous journey

04:39.280 --> 04:40.846
     that lies ahead of us.

04:40.848 --> 04:44.883
      We sail to adventure
        or our very doom.

04:46.486 --> 04:48.987
         I have no idea
       what you just said,

04:48.989 --> 04:52.424
      but your wardrobe is
     delightfully seaworthy!

04:57.363 --> 05:00.899
       Despite Applejack's
   colorful seafarer attitude,

05:00.901 --> 05:03.402
     I was still determined
        to get my friends

05:03.404 --> 05:05.470
      out of their element
        by providing them

05:05.472 --> 05:08.440
    with all the refinements
       of a luxury cruise.

05:08.442 --> 05:10.742
   I'd made sure to bring the
     most delectable nibbles

05:10.744 --> 05:12.411
       for them to enjoy.

05:12.413 --> 05:13.979
   Oooh. I brought food, too!

05:16.382 --> 05:19.051
   Let's see, I've got cotton
  candy, taffy, circus peanuts

05:19.053 --> 05:21.887
        and lots of other
       super-yummy stuff.

05:21.889 --> 05:25.757
    Oooh Pinkie Pie, that all
  looks positively delectable,

05:25.759 --> 05:29.328
   but you simply must try one
  of these cucumber sandwiches.

05:29.330 --> 05:30.495
Dig in!

05:30.497 --> 05:36.735
              Hmmm.

05:36.737 --> 05:38.937
  Arrgh! Get those off me ship!

05:38.939 --> 05:40.839
            [splash]

05:40.841 --> 05:43.041
           [bubbling]

05:43.043 --> 05:45.010
              Ohh, I'm so sorry.

05:45.012 --> 05:48.613
   I had no idea you had such
     distaste for cucumbers!

05:48.615 --> 05:51.983
        Yar-har-har-har!
       Hardy-har-har-har.

05:53.920 --> 05:56.588
            Hmmm. That doesn't
           sound like Applejack.

05:56.590 --> 06:00.025
          Well, hold on, because
            it gets even worse.

06:00.027 --> 06:01.893
         Pinkie tried to
        lighten the mood

06:01.895 --> 06:03.628
          with some fun
         maritime games.

06:06.466 --> 06:10.502
   It's Piñata O'clock! Wanna
    give it a whack, Rarity?

06:10.504 --> 06:12.104
     Oh, darling, of course!

06:12.106 --> 06:15.474
[thunderclap and whistling wind]

06:15.476 --> 06:18.710
        Har-har! Har-har!

06:18.712 --> 06:20.645
       I'll be chartin' a
    course to the very heart

06:20.647 --> 06:21.947
       of that maelstrom.

06:21.949 --> 06:27.786
       <i>♪ [dramatic music] </i>

06:27.788 --> 06:30.756
                 Uh, Applejack?
                 Just a thought,

06:30.758 --> 06:34.659
   but maybe we should steer the
    ship toward calmer waters.

06:34.661 --> 06:38.764
  This be the only
way to Plunder Cove.

06:38.766 --> 06:41.533
[thunder crack]

06:41.535 --> 06:45.170
        [crashing waves]

06:45.172 --> 06:47.873
     Perhaps if I take a quick
  look-see at that map of yours,

06:47.875 --> 06:50.142
          I could find us a more
           cruise-friendly path.

06:50.144 --> 06:52.844
There'll be no mutiny
aboard me ship!

06:52.846 --> 06:56.415
         Look at me! I'm
        the captain too!

06:56.417 --> 06:59.718
  <i>Clearly Pinkie Pie had caught</i>
     <i>Applejack's sea madness.</i>

06:59.720 --> 07:01.720
      [squeals and grunts]

07:03.990 --> 07:06.625
       <i>♪ [dramatic music] </i>

07:06.627 --> 07:11.863
       Is that all you've
       got? Yar-hahah-HAR!

07:11.865 --> 07:13.799
            [whoosh]

07:13.801 --> 07:15.600
Then what happened!?

07:15.602 --> 07:17.602
  Oh, the boat sank, obviously.

07:22.942 --> 07:26.511
          So, Applejack got some
           sort of "sea madness"

07:26.513 --> 07:29.114
                 and caused the
                boat to capsize?

07:29.116 --> 07:31.883
   After all the effort I put
  in to provide her and Pinkie

07:31.885 --> 07:33.552
      with the exact luxury
       cruise they needed

07:33.554 --> 07:34.986
          to get out of
         their elements,

07:34.988 --> 07:38.023
           that is how
      Applejack thanked me.

07:38.025 --> 07:40.592
       So, you were stuck out in
       the middle of the ocean?

07:40.594 --> 07:42.894
        How in Equestria
        did you get back?

07:42.896 --> 07:46.698
     Spike, darling, you'll
       have to forgive me.

07:46.700 --> 07:48.567
     I'm far too emotionally
       drained to discuss

07:48.569 --> 07:50.635
     the matter any further.

07:50.637 --> 07:53.138
     Rarity? I don't suppose
       there's any chance

07:53.140 --> 07:57.676
  you might be uh, exaggerating
      things just a little?

07:57.678 --> 08:01.780
   Well! I can assure you that
 that is exactly what happened.

08:01.782 --> 08:05.150
    And if you don't believe
   me, you can ask Pinkie Pie.

08:05.152 --> 08:08.186
     I am quite certain her
     story will be the same.

08:08.188 --> 08:11.857
   So, that's what Rarity said
   happened on the boat, huh?

08:15.094 --> 08:18.230
     We thought there was a
  chance she might have [ahem]

08:18.232 --> 08:21.099
         embellished the
        story just a tad.

08:21.101 --> 08:23.502
   So we wanted to hear about
     what happened from you.

08:23.504 --> 08:26.171
      Did Applejack really
        capsize the boat?

08:26.173 --> 08:28.907
         Of course not!
       That's just silly.

08:28.909 --> 08:31.610
    There's no way Applejack
    could have sank the boat.

08:31.612 --> 08:32.777
                    I knew it!

08:32.779 --> 08:34.212
That's a relief.

08:34.214 --> 08:36.181
 Because Rarity did!

08:36.183 --> 08:37.582
       What?!

08:37.583 --> 08:39.650
  It all started on the docks.

08:41.687 --> 08:43.755
        I knew Rarity and
     Applejack wanted to get

08:43.756 --> 08:45.957
    out of their element, so
    I figured I'd throw them

08:45.959 --> 08:48.727
      the funnest, silliest
        boat party ever.

08:48.729 --> 08:50.996
       But I guess Rarity
        had other ideas.

08:54.200 --> 08:56.768
      <i>I thought I overpacked</i>
        <i>until I saw Rarity</i>

08:56.770 --> 08:59.104
         <i>and her team of</i>
          <i>porter ponies.</i>

09:01.240 --> 09:04.075
       Prepare yourselves
      for a luxury cruise!

09:04.077 --> 09:07.178
       A day of opulence,
   decadence and extravagance!

09:07.180 --> 09:09.214
        [gulls squawking]

09:09.216 --> 09:10.849
                That sounds fun.

09:10.851 --> 09:14.152
Ahoy, mateys! Batten
down the hatches, ya'll

09:14.154 --> 09:17.923
'cause this here's gonna be
a boat ride of adventure!

09:17.925 --> 09:19.591
           I can live with that.

09:21.861 --> 09:24.996
       <i>♪ [military march] </i>

09:29.802 --> 09:31.970
   Huh. They just keep coming.

09:31.972 --> 09:37.709
   <i>Now you can't throw a silly</i>
    <i>boat party without snacks,</i>

09:37.711 --> 09:40.011
      <i>so I made sure to pack</i>
      <i>the funnest party food</i>

09:40.013 --> 09:41.212
          <i>I could find.</i>

09:43.082 --> 09:45.750
     Rarity? Would you care
     for some cotton candy?

09:45.752 --> 09:48.620
       It's freshly spun!

09:48.622 --> 09:53.625
    Oh, Pinkie Pie, those all
  look simply... well, simple.

09:53.627 --> 09:56.061
      But they're obviously
   unfit for a luxury cruise.

09:59.932 --> 10:02.734
   Now my cucumber sandwiches
      on the other hoof...

10:02.736 --> 10:05.203
Try one. Then you'll understand.

10:06.739 --> 10:08.807
Oh, are those
chocolate-chip?

10:10.610 --> 10:11.810
            [splash]

10:12.778 --> 10:15.814
           [bubbling]

10:15.816 --> 10:18.883
   Sorry, cucumber sandwiches
     are so ten seconds ago.

10:18.885 --> 10:22.754
     Wait, wait, wait. That
   doesn't sound like Rarity.

10:22.756 --> 10:24.889
    Just wait until you hear
    how much more unlike her

10:24.891 --> 10:26.391
           she sounds!

10:26.393 --> 10:28.126
      I thought I'd lighten
       the mood with some

10:28.128 --> 10:30.629
   super-fun party boat games.

10:30.631 --> 10:35.000
        But Rarity was a
        real wet blanket.

10:35.002 --> 10:38.937
  It's Piñata Time! Oooh! Wanna
    give it a whack, Rarity?

10:38.939 --> 10:42.841
       [derisive laughter]

10:42.843 --> 10:46.111
      Oh, you were serious.
     Well, that's adorable.

10:48.015 --> 10:53.385
  That's the spirit. Let's get
    this boat party started!

10:56.956 --> 11:00.825
          Whoa, doggy!

11:00.827 --> 11:02.827
          [thunderclap]

11:02.829 --> 11:08.733
       <i>♪ [dramatic music] </i>

11:08.735 --> 11:10.902
            [splash]

11:10.904 --> 11:14.305
      [squeals and grunts]

11:14.307 --> 11:16.675
 Tug of war? Now we're talking!

11:18.878 --> 11:20.879
      Whoever wins gets to
           be captain!

11:20.881 --> 11:26.317
      [screams and growls]

11:26.319 --> 11:28.920
       Or one of us could
      just be captain now.

11:32.958 --> 11:36.961
      Oh don't worry, dear.
   Luxury cruises never sink!

11:36.963 --> 11:37.996
    What?!

11:40.266 --> 11:42.467
            [whoosh]

11:42.469 --> 11:44.402
         And that's why
        the boat sinking

11:44.404 --> 11:47.105
     was all Rarity's fault.

11:47.107 --> 11:51.443
     That seems odd. I mean,
    we trust you, of course,

11:51.445 --> 11:54.813
         but it's all so
         extraordinary.

11:54.815 --> 11:57.449
     Oh, it's extraordinary,
           all right.

11:57.451 --> 12:00.985
     In fact, the only thing
    I might have gotten wrong

12:00.987 --> 12:02.787
       was that there were
    even MORE porter ponies.

12:02.789 --> 12:04.989
    But just to be safe, you
    should talk to Applejack.

12:04.991 --> 12:07.726
  She'll know exactly how many
    porter ponies there were.

12:07.728 --> 12:11.463
    OK, but if the boat sank,
  how did you all get rescued?

12:11.465 --> 12:13.498
   Oh, that's easy. We just...

12:13.500 --> 12:16.468
      [scream] My muffins!

12:16.470 --> 12:19.738
     That's it. We've got to
      go talk to Applejack.

12:19.740 --> 12:21.940
        Good idea. She'll
      straighten this out.

12:21.942 --> 12:24.342
  I just really, really want to
   know how they made it back.

12:24.344 --> 12:26.177
 But yeah, that'd be great, too.

12:29.448 --> 12:33.151
   Hold on a tick. Pinkie Pie
    says it's Rarity's fault

12:33.153 --> 12:35.820
        And Rarity says I
         sank the boat?

12:35.822 --> 12:37.956
    Well, that's plum crazy.

12:37.958 --> 12:40.859
 If you two really want to know
  what happened, I'll tell ya.

12:40.861 --> 12:42.927
      Y'all know how Pinkie
    Pie and Rarity wanted to

12:42.929 --> 12:46.965
 Well, I brought a treasure map
   to give 'em a rip-roaring,

12:46.967 --> 12:49.868
      seafaring adventure!

12:49.870 --> 12:52.937
    <i>But they had other ideas.</i>

12:52.939 --> 12:55.440
        La-la-la! Prepare
     yourselves for the most

12:55.442 --> 12:59.010
      luxurious boat outing
     that ever outed a boat!

13:01.046 --> 13:04.449
      And more fun than you
      can shake a stick at

13:04.451 --> 13:07.252
   because I brought a stick!

13:07.254 --> 13:10.288
   All right, mateys. But just
     y'all wait till you see

13:10.290 --> 13:12.857
     the high-seas adventure
        I've got planned.

13:24.270 --> 13:27.305
       <i>Unfortunately, they</i>
      <i>seemed less interested</i>

13:27.307 --> 13:31.409
       <i>and more interested</i>
            <i>in snacks.</i>

13:34.380 --> 13:36.981
Oh darling, that food
isn't fit for a pony

13:36.983 --> 13:39.551
of proper breeding, darling
and refinement, darling.

13:39.553 --> 13:41.452
   Now my cucumber sandwiches
      on the other hoof...

13:43.122 --> 13:45.089
             Betcha I can fit
           them all in my mouth!

13:46.525 --> 13:47.859
    Pinkie, darling, please!

13:47.861 --> 13:49.427
       [chomp chomp chomp]

13:49.429 --> 13:51.930
            Uh-oooh!

13:51.932 --> 13:53.331
              Agh!

13:53.333 --> 13:54.999
            [splash]

13:55.001 --> 13:57.869
           [bubbling]

13:57.871 --> 14:00.538
Rarity, I--

14:00.540 --> 14:03.408
          Well, I never! Humpha!

14:03.410 --> 14:05.343
             Me neither! Humpha!

14:08.280 --> 14:10.248
       Do you want to say
         it or should I?

14:10.250 --> 14:14.285
     That sure doesn't sound
   like Rarity or Pinkie Pie.

14:14.287 --> 14:16.387
       Oh, it gets a sight
        worse than that.

14:19.058 --> 14:23.394
          It's P.W.T.!
      Piñata-whacking time!

14:23.396 --> 14:26.931
     Oh, darling, "whacking"
        is a base pastime

14:26.933 --> 14:30.268
   for common ponies, doesn't
    interest me in the least.

14:32.872 --> 14:33.972
              Meh.

14:36.408 --> 14:37.408
                   Hee hee!

14:37.410 --> 14:38.476
              Huh?

14:43.215 --> 14:45.884
        Whoa, whoa, whoa.

14:45.886 --> 14:47.318
          [thunderclap]

14:49.021 --> 14:51.022
        [whistling wind]

14:51.024 --> 14:52.624
       Looks like we need
        to change course.

14:55.227 --> 14:57.528
      Oooh! Why, this will
    make a perfect tablecloth

14:57.530 --> 14:59.464
      for my cheese board.

14:59.466 --> 15:02.967
   Maybe so, but it's also the
 only way to find Thunder Cove!

15:02.969 --> 15:04.535
           [giggling]

15:04.537 --> 15:06.471
       And Pinkie Pie was
      just about as helpful

15:06.473 --> 15:08.473
   as a weasel in a hen house.

15:08.475 --> 15:11.342
       Captain Pinkie Pie
     reporting for map duty!

15:11.344 --> 15:13.278
            [squeals]

15:13.280 --> 15:14.545
            [splash]

15:14.547 --> 15:20.351
       <i>♪ [dramatic music] </i>

15:20.353 --> 15:22.287
       Hold on, everypony!

15:23.555 --> 15:24.656
            [whoosh]

15:26.926 --> 15:30.061
Wait, so it was Rarity
  and Pinkie's fault?

15:30.063 --> 15:33.331
  Yup. And maybe if
they ever apologize,

15:33.333 --> 15:35.166
I'll consider talking
   to them again.

15:37.470 --> 15:41.706
  I don't know how we're going
   to get them to talk again.

15:41.708 --> 15:44.442
    Neither do I,
Spike. Neither do I.

15:47.479 --> 15:50.548
               ♪

15:50.550 --> 15:53.451
   There's got to be some way
   to fix this. If Applejack,

15:53.453 --> 15:56.120
   Pinkie Pie, and Rarity keep
   not talking to each other,

15:56.122 --> 15:58.623
   they could forget what good
    friends they really are.

15:58.625 --> 16:00.458
      I just don't get it.

16:00.460 --> 16:03.261
      All of their stories
        are so different.

16:03.263 --> 16:06.698
   We're never going to figure
    out what really happened.

16:06.700 --> 16:08.599
  Their stories were different,

16:08.601 --> 16:11.369
        but they also had
        a lot in common.

16:11.371 --> 16:14.973
    I guess. They were all on
     a ship that sank and...

16:14.975 --> 16:16.240
        that's about it.

16:16.242 --> 16:17.442
           Not quite.

16:17.444 --> 16:20.578
               ♪

16:24.683 --> 16:28.553
   Ah-ha! Not only do I think
    I know how the boat sank,

16:28.555 --> 16:31.456
    I have a pretty good idea
  how to get Rarity, Applejack,

16:31.458 --> 16:33.257
  and Pinkie Pie back together!

16:38.197 --> 16:40.565
I hope this plan of yours works.

16:42.701 --> 16:45.236
   Winona brought me your note
  about a friendship emergency.

16:45.238 --> 16:47.505
         How can I help?

16:47.507 --> 16:49.173
      Opalescence delivered
     your message, Twilight.

16:49.175 --> 16:54.012
  It's a good thing it was time
  for Gummy's bath, or I might

16:54.014 --> 16:56.014
  not have seen your note about
    the emergency, Twilight.

16:57.282 --> 16:59.584
     What's she doing here?

16:59.586 --> 17:01.786
Sorry, but I just
didn't know how else

17:01.788 --> 17:03.654
to get the three of
you here together.

17:03.656 --> 17:07.759
And there really is a
friendship emergency. Yours!

17:07.761 --> 17:12.262
  Oh, there's no emergency. I'm
  just waiting for an apology.

17:12.265 --> 17:13.798
           An apology?

17:13.800 --> 17:16.634
       Why would you want
        me to apologize,

17:16.636 --> 17:18.569
   when it was Rarity's fault?

17:18.570 --> 17:22.173
Applejack clearly
caused the boat to sink!

17:22.175 --> 17:24.474
She stranded us in the
middle of the ocean!

17:24.477 --> 17:28.279
    UGH! Will somepony please
  tell me how you made it back?

17:31.417 --> 17:33.317
           [gurgling]

17:40.592 --> 17:44.395
Well, maybe it wasn't
the middle of the ocean.

17:44.397 --> 17:48.399
   Even so, I don't appreciate
       being hornswoggled

17:48.401 --> 17:50.735
     into coming back here.

17:50.737 --> 17:52.437
On that, at
least we agree.

17:52.439 --> 17:58.176
    on how the boat capsized
     and blame each other...

17:58.178 --> 18:00.211
       but if you come on
        the boat with me,

18:00.213 --> 18:01.612
       I'll show you what
        really happened.

18:03.849 --> 18:06.384
Well, not that I
have any doubt,

18:06.386 --> 18:08.453
but it will feel good for
everypony to see exactly

18:08.455 --> 18:10.688
whose fault it was.

18:10.690 --> 18:12.523
         I think we all
        know which pony's

18:12.525 --> 18:14.725
    about to be proven right.

18:15.761 --> 18:18.696
           We sure do!

18:18.698 --> 18:21.099
       Like I said, I sure
        hope this works.

18:26.105 --> 18:27.738
          Heh heh heh.

18:27.740 --> 18:31.609
  Whatever you're looking for,
    I hope you find it soon.

18:31.611 --> 18:35.480
    Don't worry, Spike. I've
    got it all under control.

18:35.482 --> 18:37.748
    While all of your stories
     seemed very different,

18:37.750 --> 18:41.486
    they all had something in
  common. Cucumber sandwiches!

18:44.790 --> 18:47.325
What in the hay does that
have to do with anything?

18:47.559 --> 18:49.560
            [splash]

18:49.562 --> 18:52.663
    And why would you waste a
  perfectly good hors d'oeuvre?

18:52.665 --> 18:54.599
             You also mentioned
             the bubbling water.

18:57.836 --> 18:59.370
         And the swell.

18:59.372 --> 19:02.807
      Cucumber just happens
     to be the favorite food

19:02.809 --> 19:06.811
  of the Tri-horned Bunyip. And
  bubbles, followed by a swell

19:06.813 --> 19:08.846
    is what happens when they
     swim up to the shallows

19:08.848 --> 19:11.382
        from deep water!

19:11.384 --> 19:15.586
  So, we attracted a tri-horned
       whatchamacallit...

19:15.588 --> 19:17.722
With cucumber
sandwiches?

19:17.724 --> 19:19.657
     Sounds like a stretch.

19:21.326 --> 19:22.927
       Hello, Bunyip, sir.

19:28.867 --> 19:30.735
         So that's a...

19:30.737 --> 19:32.336
          A Tri-horned Bunyip...

19:32.338 --> 19:34.238
                Who's very sorry
                 he accidentally

19:34.240 --> 19:36.474
               knocked over your
                 boat, right?

19:38.410 --> 19:41.646
   Wait; the storm had nothing
    to do with the capsizing?

19:41.648 --> 19:46.217
  All right. Even if our friend
    the Bunyip is responsible

19:46.219 --> 19:50.755
    that still doesn't excuse
   a certain pony's behavior.

19:50.757 --> 19:53.858
              Me!? How about you
                and Pinkie Pie?

19:53.860 --> 19:56.327
     Pfft! Wha-?! How- ME?--

19:56.329 --> 19:57.962
     Twilight: I think I can
        explain that too.

19:57.964 --> 20:00.598
    Each one of you spent so
   much time trying to come up

20:00.600 --> 20:02.433
      with the perfect way
        to get the others

20:02.435 --> 20:04.302
      out of their element,
     that you didn't notice

20:04.304 --> 20:06.370
        your friends were
      doing the same thing.

20:06.372 --> 20:10.908
 Wait a minute. You brought all
 those games and things for us?

20:10.910 --> 20:13.744
  Of course! I figured the boat
    trip was the perfect time

20:13.746 --> 20:16.447
        to do things that
       were silly and fun.

20:16.449 --> 20:18.983
And I was just trying
to give the two of you

20:18.985 --> 20:21.652
the elegant cruise I
thought you deserved.

20:21.654 --> 20:25.223
   And I just wanted to give you
    two a high seas adventure,

20:25.225 --> 20:27.892
      since that'd be something
    new and different for y'all.

20:27.894 --> 20:30.561
          OOOOHHHHHHH.

20:30.563 --> 20:32.730
        That is so sweet.

20:32.732 --> 20:34.999
       You must have gone
    through so much trouble.

20:35.001 --> 20:37.301
     Well, not half as much
       trouble as you did

20:37.303 --> 20:40.905
   making all that fancy food.
  And bringing all those games.

20:40.907 --> 20:43.674
  I guess this just teaches us
   that even longtime friends

20:43.676 --> 20:45.910
 need to work at communication.

20:45.912 --> 20:47.712
     Well, there's something
     I'd like to communicate

20:47.714 --> 20:49.580
      to you all right now.

20:49.582 --> 20:53.351
 You girls are the best friends
     a pony could ever have.

20:53.353 --> 20:55.786
Oh, let's never
fight again!

20:55.788 --> 20:56.887
                   Agreed.

20:56.889 --> 20:57.755
         You've got it!

20:57.757 --> 20:59.624
[growl]

20:59.626 --> 21:02.026
       All right, you big
       softy. Bring it in.

21:07.032 --> 21:10.668
        Come on, Bunyip,
       sir. You've got it!

21:10.670 --> 21:13.804
               ♪

21:19.479 --> 21:23.848
     There's nothing like a
 luxurious adventure boat party

21:23.850 --> 21:25.750
 to get you out of your element.

21:27.953 --> 21:30.288
Spike: You said it!

